--- !u!114 &48360877
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 48360872}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5d7d578828bcc48f1a48dee4743510bf, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogueHandler
  npcName: Thalen
  interactPrompt: Press E to talk
  dialogueLines:
  - "Easy now\u2026 you\u2019re lucky to be breathing.\nMost who fall from that storm
    never wake again."
  - "You\u2019ve arrived in Elementara\u2026 though I doubt it was by choice."
  - "That storm you sailed through\u2026 it is no ordinary storm.\nIt is a cage.
    And now, you are trapped inside it."
  - "A warlord named Zerath has claimed this island.\nHe did not conquer it with
    armies\u2026 but with the elements themselves."
  - "Once, four shrines kept this land in harmony\u2026\nFire, Water, Earth, and
    Lightning.\n\nNow they are corrupted\u2026 twisted into sources of power for
    Zerath."
  - "His generals guard each shrine\u2026\nPyronis of Flame\u2026 Aqualis of Tide\u2026
    Voltaris of Storm\u2026 Terradon of Earth.\n\nDefeat them\u2026 and you weaken
    Zerath."
  - "But raw strength alone will not save you.\n\nThe elements follow a cycle\u2026\nEarth
    shatters Lightning\u2026\nLightning cuts through Water\u2026\nWater extinguishes
    Fire\u2026\nFire consumes Earth."
  - "Reclaim the shrines\u2026 restore their balance\u2026\nOnly then will the storm
    break\u2026 and your path home open."
  - "You didn\u2019t choose to come here\u2026\nBut you may be the only one who can
    leave."
  dialoguePanel: {fileID: 389568975}
  speakerNameText: {fileID: 1220997353}
  dialogueBodyText: {fileID: 1470355963}
